{"/service/ndnp/nmu/batch_nmu_huxley_ver01/data/sn84020630/0041615028A/1908051801/0121.xml":{"full_text":"r\nMONDAY, MAY 18, 1908.\nSANTA, m Km MEXICAN. OANTA FE. N. IX\nPAGE THREE\nTIME TABLE ALL LINES.\nEntering and Leaving Santa Fe Com\npiled According to Schedule\nof Trains Now In Effect.\nSANTA FE CENTRAL.\nNo 1. Southbound leaves Santa Fe\n12:50 p. m.\nNo. 2.Northbound arrives Santa eF\n0:25 p. m.\nDENVER RIO GRANDE.\nNo. 426 Eastbound leaves Santa\nFo 10:45 a. m.\nNo. 425 Westbound arrives Santa\nFe 4:15 p. m.\nATCHISON, TOPEKA SANTA GE\nLamy Branch.\nArrive at Santa Fe Station.\nNo. 721 11:10 a. m.\nNo. 723 C:50 p. m.\nNo. 725 10:55 p. m.\nDepart From Santa Fe Station.\nNo. 720 8:25 a. m.\nNo. 722 4:20 p. m.\nNo. 724 7:40 p. m\nNo. 720 connects with Nos. 10 and\n2, east and No. 3, limited, west, at\nLamy.\nNo. 722 connects with No. 1, west,\nat Lamy.\nNo. 7 carries El Paso sleeper.\nNo. 724 connects with Nos. 7 and 9,\nwestbound, and Noa. 4 and 8 east\nbound.\nMain Line Via Lamy.\nNo. 7 will stop at all stations. Lamy\nto Albuquerque to discharge passen\ngers from Santa Fe.\nNo. 721 leaves Lamy at 10:10 a. m.,\nand will not wait for No. 2 from the\nwest at Lamy, waiting only for No. 10\nfrom the south, and No. 3 from the\neast.\nThe New Mexican Printing company\nhas ready and for sale up-to-date and\ncorrect compilations of the territorial\nIncorporaLon laws, price 75 cents; of\nthe territorial road laws, price 60\ncents; and of the territorial mining\nlaws, price TO cents per copy. These\ncan be purchased by applying In per\nson or by mall at the office of the company.\nNEW MEXICO REPORTS\nVOLUME NUMBER 13\nJust Issued From Press of New Mexi\ncan Printing Company Essential\nto Every Attorney.\nVolume 13, of the reports of cases\nargued and determined la the su\npremo court of New Mexico la now\nready for distribution among the mem\nbers of the bar. No law library In New\nMoxlco Is complete without It and to\nthe practicing attorney It Is absolutely\nnecessary. Justices of the pence, U. S.\ncommissioners, court officials and all\nothers who are Interested In\nthe Interpretation of the law,\nespecially the New Mexico law,\nby the highest court of the territory,\nshould have the volume at their el\nbow. It Is compiled by Judgo A. J.\nAbbott, the supremo court reporter,\nand federal attorney for the Pueblo\nIndians, and his experience on the\nbench, as practicing attorney and as\nthe author of previous volumes of Re\nports, assures that volume 13 has been\ncarefully edited and Indexed. The ty\npographical work and binding Is by\nthe New Mexican Printing company\nwhich is being complimented upon the\nfact that It Is tho best printed and\nbest bound volume of New Mexico Re\nports thus far Issued. The price per\nvolume, $2.70, Is lower than that of\nany previous volume To this 30 cents\nshould be added for postago, If volume\nIs ordered by mall. The edition Is lim\nited and orders will bo filled In the\nsequence of their receipt.\nHeadquarters for wedding cards and\nannouncements, at the New Mexican\nPrinting company, Santa Fe.\nWALL PAPER\nWALL PAPER\nA rronto for Peats and Ameri.\nH0IU& can wan paper Co.\nAH Tie Newest Desips.\nLORENZO AND DI6NE0.\nm Famous Falstaff Beer\nHENRY KRICK\nSole Agent for\nLENIP'S ST. LOUIS BEER\nAnd Ml Kinds of Mineral Water.\nSODA WATER,\nAny Flavor you Doslre\nOrim Filltfl tor Any Amount. Wail Order\ntll Raceiv Prompt Attention\nBad Attack of Dysentery Cured.\n\"An honored citizen of this town\nwas suffering from a severe attack 'tf\ndysentery. He told a f lend if ho could\nobtain a bottle of Chamberlain's Colic,\nCholera and Diarrhoea Remedy, .to\nfelt confident cf being cured, ho hav\ning used this remedy In tho West. He\nwas told that I kept It In stock and\nlost no time In obtaining it, and was\npromptly cured,\" Hays M. J. Leach,\ndruggist, of Wolcott, Vt. For sale by\nall druggists.\nTO AND FROM ROSWELL.\nConnection made with Automobile\nLine at Torrance for Roswell dally.\nAutomobile leaves Torrance for Ito\nwell at 4 a. m., and arrives at Roswell\nat 12, noon. Automobile leaves Ros\nwell for Torrance at 1 p. m., and ar\nrives at Torrance at 10 p. m. The fare\nbetween Santa Fe and Torrance Is\n$5.80 and between Torrance and Ros\nwell, $10.00. Reserve seats on automo\nbile by wire. J. W. Stockard, manag\ner Automobile Line.\nDeWltt's Little Karly Risers are\nsmall, safe, sure and gentle little pills.\nSold by The Ireland Pharmacy.\nVISITING CARDS.\nEngraved cards ce viste and wed\nding invitations a specialty at the New\nMexican printing office. Any one\nstanding in need of such will do well\nto call at this office and examine sam\nples, style of work and prices.\nPhone 38.\nBontajuiT Avtnui.\nKennedy's Laxative Cough Syrup\ndoes not constipate, but on the other\nhand Us laxative principles gently\nmove the bowels. Children like it. Sold\nby The Ireland Pharmacy.\nThe New Mexican can do printing\nequal to that done in any of the large\ncities. Our solicitor: Every piece of\nwork we turn out. Try our stock once\nand you will certainly come again. We\nhave all the facilities for turning out\nevery class of work, Including one of\nthe best binderies In the West.\nPS ilpiegelberg-\n527 San Francisco Street.\ninoian anil Wean Weres m Curies\nBlankets, Baskets, Wax, Feather and Linen Drawn Work,\nOpals, Turquoise, Garnets and Other Gems\nOUR MOTTO: To Have the Best of Everything in Our Line.\n0J0 CALJEflTE ffOT SPRINGS.\nThese celebrated Hot Springs are lo\ncated in the midst of the Ancient Cliff\nDwellings, twenty-five miles west of\nTaos, and fifty miles north of Santa\nFe, and about twelve miles from Bar\nanco Station, on the Denver and Rio\nGrande Railroad, from which point a\ndally line of stage runs to the springs.\nThe temperature of these waters, is\nfrom 90 to 122 degrees. The gases are\ncarbonic. Altitude 6,000 feet. Climate\nvery dry and delightful the entire year\nround. There Is now a commodious ho\ntel for the convenience of invalids and\ntourists. People suffering from Con\nsumption, cancer, and other contagi\nous diseases, are not accepted. These\nwaters contain 1,626.24 grains of alka\nline salts to the gallon, being the rich\nest alkalin Hot Springs In the world.\nThe efficiency of these waters has\nbeen thoroughly tested by the mirac\nulous cures attested to in the follow\ning diseases:. Paralysis, Rheumatism\nNeuralgia, Malaria, Bright's Disease\nof the Kidneys, Syphilitic and Mercur\nial Affections, Scrofula, Catarrh, La\nGrippe, all Female Complaints, etc.\nBoard, lodging and bathing $2.50 per\nday; $15 per week; $50 per month.\nStage meets Denver trains and waits\nfor Santa Fe train upon request. This\nresort is attractive at all seasons and\nis open all winter. Passengers for OJo\nCaliente can leave Santa Fe at 9 a. m.\nand reach Ojo Caliente at 4 p. m., the\nsame day. For further particulars address:\nANTONIO JOSEPH, Proprietor.\nOJo Caliente, Taos County, rt M\nKodaks and Photo Supplies\nART PICTURES AND FRAMING\nWe make a specialty of DEVELOPING, PRINT\nING and ENLARGING. Mall Orders Given Prompt\nAttention. Send for Catalogue.\nHOWLAND A DEWEY COMPANY,\n610 S. Broadway, Las Angeles, Calif.\nSffllFIlA\nAH ld\nINHERITANCE 3\nOF DISEASE AND SUFFERING\nNo truth is more forcibly manifested ia physical life than the old saying\nlike begets like for just as the offspring of healthy ancestry are blessed\nwith pure, rich blood, insuring health and strength, so the children of blood\ntainted parentage inherit a polluted circulation to burden their existence\nwith disease and suffering. Swollen glands about the neck, brittle bones,\nweak eyes, pale, waxy complexions, running sores and ulcers and general\npoor health, are the usual ways in which Scrofula is manifested. In some\ncases the blood i3 so filled with the scrofulous germs and tubercular matter\nthat from birth life is made miserable with suffering. Others who inherit\nthe disease succeed in holding the trouble in check during young, vigorous\nlife, but when the system ha3 begun to weaken and lose its natural vitality,\nand especially after a spell of sickness, the ravages of the disease will com\nmence, and ia a great many cases terminate in Consumption. S. S. S. is the\nvery best treatment for Scrofula. It renovates the entire circulation and\ndrives out the scrofulous and tubercular\ndeposits. S. S. S. is the greatest of all blood\npurifiers, and it not only goes to the very\nbottom of the trouble and removes the cause\nand cures the disease, but it supplies the\nweak, anaemic blood with the healthful\nproperties it is in need of. S. S. S. is mad\nentirely of healing, cleansing roots, herbi\nand barks, and is an absolutely safe remedy for young or old. Book oa\nthe blood and any medical advice about Scrofula given free of charge.\nTHE SWIFT SPECIFIC CO.. ATLANTA. GA.\n3\n0\nPURELY VEGETABLE\nCLAYTON HAS THE\nAUTOMOBILE FEVER\nHas an Auto Mail Route to Town of\nKenton Large Shipment of Home\nGrown Cane Seed.\nClayton, N. M., May 18. Clayton\nhas tho automobile fever In common\nwith tho rest of the New Mexico\ntowns. Tho latest Is an automobllo\nmall route to Kenton from this place.\nA car of cane seed was shipped to\nDenver hist week. Tho seed was a\nproduct of this county and was the\nfirst ever shipped out. The Indica\ntions are that after another year\npractically all of tho seed for the de\nvelopment of the farms in this terri\ntory will bo home grown.\nrrofessor O. V. Munson has been\nselected as tho principal of tho\nschools of district number 1 for the\ncoming year, with Mrs. O. P. Munson\nand Miss Esther Smith as teachers of\nthe primary grades. 1 no balanco of\nthe corps of teachers will be selected\nsoon.\nScarlet fever has boon epidemic for\nsomo time past In this city. It has\nselected several grown up people us\nits victims as well as children. It is\nbolioved that a rigid quarantine has\ntho contagion under control.\nWhile the weather has been dry\nthis spring and with not as much rain\nfall as usual, the crops are looking\nwell and give fair promise of splen\ndid yield.\nHiggins Brothers have sold their\nlivery barn to J. Sayers, who will con\nduct the business at the same stand.\nJ. A. Wasseu of Decatur, Texas, has\ndecided to locate hero.\nClayton citizens are looking for\nward with interest to the promised vis\nit of Governor George Curry and party\nin their special train, which will take\nplace the first of June. Tho gover\nnor's visit will bo largely in the Inter\nest of the Irrigation Congress which\nwill mean so much to the whole South\nwest and which meets in Albuquerque\nthis fall. A rousing reception will bo\nextended on this visit.\nTEXICO BANK TO\nERECT NEW HOME\nHandsome Structure to Be Built on\nMain Street Insurance Compa\nnies Put Up Rates\nBiliousness and Constipation.\nFor years I was troubled with bili\nousness and constipation, which made\nlife miserable for me. My appetite fail\ned me. I lost my usual force and vi\ntality. Pepsin preparations and cathar\ntics only made matters worse. I do not\nknow where I should have been today\nhad I not tried Chamberlain's Stom\nach and Liver Tablets. The tablets re\nlieve the 111 feelings at once, strength\nen the digestive functions, purify the\nstomach, liver and blood, helping the\nsystem to do its work naturally. Mrs.\nRosa Potts, Birmingham, Ala. These\ntablets are for sale by all druggists.\nTexlco, N. M., May 18. The Texlco\nNational bank has bought a quarter\nblock of land on Main street and will\nImmediately commence the construc\ntion of a flno bank building. The sec\nond story will bo used for offices. B.\nI). Oldham is tho cashier.\nL. C. Armfleld of Farwell, Texas,\nhas purchased tho J. M. Neely drug\nstore, and will personally conduct the\nbusiness In the future.\nA. J. Smith has nearly completed\nthe construction of a two-story con\ncrete business block on north Main\nstreet. The building is fire proof.\nThe insurance companies are taking\nadvantage of the poor fire fighting\nequipment of this town to put up the\nrate. Tho companies charge ten dol\nlars n hundred for insurance on Main\nstreet.\nO. M. Ourley, of Allen county, Kan-1\nsas, has purchased tho A. E. White\nhead farm, eight miles southwest of\nhere for S3.3C0. Tho farm comprises\n4S5 acres.\nP. T. Schwebel has sold his meat\nmarket to L. W. Rook, formerly of\nSulphur, Oklahoma.\nSubscriptions for bank stock in a\nnew bank to be started at Grady, a\ntown about forty miles north of Texl\nco, which has no railway connections,\nare being solicited by C. C, Marshall,\ntho promoter.\nA naa Yogas m\n1 Ml \"V I 7nrI( I\nIf fiKstaocla 09\nI V S\nSTUDY THE MAP.\nThe natural point on the new A. T. S. F. Cut-Off for the distribution of\nfreight, having the advantage of the easy grades and short route to the\nEast and West ,and direct communication with all points in the Ttrritory.\nWholesale houses are coming to Willard as soon as the Cut-Off Is open. Sur\nrounded by a fine farming country. The purest water in New Mexico. The\ngeographical center of Torrance county and of New Mexico. The water\npoint on the great A. T. S. F. short line through New Mexico, Willard li\na growing town. Willard will make a city. Study the map. For Information\ncall or address\nFRANK L. WALRATH, RfcAL\" ESTATE,-.\nWillard. New Mexico.\nKodol completely digests all classes\nof food. It will get right at the trouble\nand do the very work Itself for the\nstomach. It is pleasant to take. Sold\nby The Ireland Pharmacy.\nBUYS LAND IN\nSISTER REPUBLIC\nJ. S. Fltzhugh, Prominent Attorney of\nClovis, Interested in 50,000 Acre\nTract Near Tamplco.\nMULES DROWNED IN\nSWOLLEN STREAM\nRoosevelt County Ranchman Loses\nFine Span and Narrowly Escapes\nDeath Himself.\nPortales, N. M., May 18. Heavy\nrains in Spring Valley township dur\ning the past few days has raised the\nwater high in Stillwater creek, mak\ning fording very hazardous. On Sat\nurday last while W. Standley, a ranch\nman was attempting to ford the creek\nnear hero his wagon was overturned\nIn mid-stream and a fine span of mules\nwere swept away, both being drowned.\nStandley after much difficulty manag\ned to affect a landing a quarter of a\nmile down stream.\nDr. H. R. Thomas of Sulphur\nSprings, Arkansas, has opened an of\nfice and will practice his profession\nhere.\nFrank Warmica has purchased the\nStewart livery stable and will con\ntinue the busluess.\nJ. P. Stone, president of the Citizens\nNational Bank, has returned home\nfrom Mineral Wells, Texas, where he\nhas been for the past month recuper\nating from a serious Illness.\nThe business outlook for Roosevelt\ncounty has never been better. The\nrange Is in excellent shape. The stock\nmen are encouraged and all spring\ncrops are giving promise of a thrifty\nharvest.\nClovis, N. M., May IS. J. S. Fltz\nhugh, a prominent attorney of this\nplace has just returned from a trip\ninto the southern part of. Mexico\nwhere he Is interested in the purchase\nof a tract of 50,000 acres of land. The\nland Is about fifty miles from the\ncoast near Tamplco and Is a valuable\nagricultural and timber tract.\nJohn S. Adair enjoyed a visit from\nan old college friend, tho Rev. Robert\nM. Donaldson of Denver last week.\nThe two were on the faculty of Woost\ner College In Ohio when first acquainted.\nThe Roosevelt county telephone\nwith headquarters here is just finish\ning the construction of forty miles of\ntoll line and an exchange building at\nMelrose. The line will connect every\nj part of the county from Ellda on the\nsouth to Fort Sumner on the east.\nC. E. Harris has completed a hand\nsomo residence south of town. His\nj family have moved here from Roswell\nand will make their future home here,\nRevival meetings1 conducted by the\njRevs. J. W. Henderson and Rev; Cal\nihoun in the large tent closed the last\nof the week and the tent has been re\nmoved to Texlco. The meetings were\nwell attended.\nThe Clovis National Bank has in\nstalled an American Bank protection\nelectric alarm system and also put in\nsafety deposit boxes for rent to its\ncustomers.\nCORRICK CARRIAGE CO.\nHaek 3 luss Line\n6\n120 San Francisco St.\nCall up 132 Black for Carriages.\n4\nOUR\nPI\nAGE\nOTTO RETSCH, Ptoprietor.\nFALSTAFF BOTTLED BEER.\nANY QUALITY FROM A PINT UP.\nFine Wines, Liquors Cigars\nWEST SIDE OF PLAZA\nSANTA FE NIW\nFor anything and everything appertaining to Printing or Binding\ncall on the New Mexican Printing Company.\nMm\nWhen your food seems to nauseate\ntake Kodol. Take Kodol now and until\nyou know you are right again. There\nIsn't any doubt about what it will do\nand you will find the truth of this\nstatement verified after you have used\nKodol for a few weeks. It is sold here\nby. The Ireland Pharmacy.\nFor a burn or scald apply Cham\nberlain's Salve. It will allay the pain\nalmost instantly and quickly heal the\ninjured parts. For sale by all druggists\nVISITING CARDS.\nThe New Mexican Printing company\nis prepared to furnish cards de viste\nfor ladies and for gentlemen on short\nnotice In first class style at reason\nable prices, either engraved or print\ned. Call In the New Mexican Printing\ncompany.\nThe seals and record books for no\ntaries public for sale by the New\nMexican Printing company at very\nreasonable rates. Seals for Incor\nporated companies are also handled.\nCall at or. address the Hew Mexican\nPrinting company, Santa Fe, New\nMexloo.\nSubscribe for the Dally New Meit\ncan and get the news.\nkm\nm\nr\nThe kind that grows with your library\nthat will fit practically any space that\ncan be moved one unit at a time by one\nperson without disturbing the books that Is\npractical, artistic and the only perfect sectional\nbookcase made. Fitted with non-binding, roller\nbearing doors; base units furnished with or without\ndrawers; and all made In a variety of woods and\nfinishes adapted to any surroundings. Call and\nsee them or send for catalog 105 with interior\n\nviews showing arranmueDi injiorary spanor,eic\nNew Mexican Printing' Company\nlocal agents, Santa Fa New Mexico.\nK\ni\nAt\n't","height":"29924","width":"18760"}}
